51static const int cDefaultCacheCapacity = 8192 * 1024;
52static const Seconds cMinDelayBeforeLiveDecodedPrune { 1_s };
53static const float cTargetPrunePercentage = .95f; // Percentage of capacity toward which we prune, to avoid immediately pruning again.
54
55MemoryCache& MemoryCache::singleton()
56{
57 ASSERT(WTF::isMainThread());
58 static NeverDestroyed<MemoryCache> memoryCache;
59 return memoryCache;
60}
61
62MemoryCache::MemoryCache()
63 : m_capacity(cDefaultCacheCapacity)
64 , m_maxDeadCapacity(cDefaultCacheCapacity)
65 , m_pruneTimer(*this, &MemoryCache::prune)
66{
67 static_assert(sizeof(long long) > sizeof(unsigned), "Numerical overflow can happen when adjusting the size of the cached memory.");
68
69 static std::once_flag onceFlag;
70 std::call_once(onceFlag, [] {
71 PAL::registerNotifyCallback("com.apple.WebKit.showMemoryCache", [] {
72 MemoryCache::singleton().dumpStats();
73 MemoryCache::singleton().dumpLRULists(true);
74 });
75 });
76}

78auto MemoryCache::sessionResourceMap(PAL::SessionID sessionID) const -> CachedResourceMap*
79{
80 ASSERT(sessionID.isValid());
81 return m_sessionResources.get(sessionID);
82}
83
84auto MemoryCache::ensureSessionResourceMap(PAL::SessionID sessionID) -> CachedResourceMap&
85{
86 ASSERT(sessionID.isValid());
87 auto& map = m_sessionResources.add(sessionID, nullptr).iterator->value;
88 if (!map)
89 map = makeUnique<CachedResourceMap>();
90 return *map;
91}
92
93bool MemoryCache::shouldRemoveFragmentIdentifier(const URL& originalURL)
94{
95 if (!originalURL.hasFragmentIdentifier())
96 return false;
97 // Strip away fragment identifier from HTTP URLs.
98 // Data URLs must be unmodified. For file and custom URLs clients may expect resources
99 // to be unique even when they differ by the fragment identifier only.
100 return originalURL.protocolIsInHTTPFamily();
101}
102
103URL MemoryCache::removeFragmentIdentifierIfNeeded(const URL& originalURL)
104{
105 if (!shouldRemoveFragmentIdentifier(originalURL))
106 return originalURL;
107 URL url = originalURL;
108 url.removeFragmentIdentifier();
109 return url;
110}
111
112bool MemoryCache::add(CachedResource& resource)
113{
114 if (disabled())
115 return false;
116
117 if (resource.resourceRequest().httpMethod() != "GET")
118 return false;
119
120 ASSERT(WTF::isMainThread());
121
122 auto key = std::make_pair(resource.url(), resource.cachePartition());
123
124 ensureSessionResourceMap(resource.sessionID()).set(key, &resource);
125 resource.setInCache(true);
126
127 resourceAccessed(resource);
128
129 LOG(ResourceLoading, "MemoryCache::add Added '%.255s', resource %p\n", resource.url().string().latin1().data(), &resource);
130 return true;
131}
132
133void MemoryCache::revalidationSucceeded(CachedResource& revalidatingResource, const ResourceResponse& response)
134{
135 ASSERT(response.source() == ResourceResponse::Source::MemoryCacheAfterValidation);
136 ASSERT(revalidatingResource.resourceToRevalidate());
137 CachedResource& resource = *revalidatingResource.resourceToRevalidate();
138 ASSERT(!resource.inCache());
139 ASSERT(resource.isLoaded());
140
141 // Calling remove() can potentially delete revalidatingResource, which we use
142 // below. This mustn't be the case since revalidation means it is loaded
143 // and so canDelete() is false.
144 ASSERT(!revalidatingResource.canDelete());
145
146 remove(revalidatingResource);
147
148 auto& resources = ensureSessionResourceMap(resource.sessionID());
149 auto key = std::make_pair(resource.url(), resource.cachePartition());
150
151 ASSERT(!resources.get(key));
152 resources.set(key, &resource);
153 resource.setInCache(true);
154 resource.updateResponseAfterRevalidation(response);
155 insertInLRUList(resource);
156 long long delta = resource.size();
157 if (resource.decodedSize() && resource.hasClients())
158 insertInLiveDecodedResourcesList(resource);
159 if (delta)
160 adjustSize(resource.hasClients(), delta);
161
162 revalidatingResource.switchClientsToRevalidatedResource();
163 ASSERT(!revalidatingResource.m_deleted);
164 // this deletes the revalidating resource
165 revalidatingResource.clearResourceToRevalidate();
166}
167
168void MemoryCache::revalidationFailed(CachedResource& revalidatingResource)
169{
170 ASSERT(WTF::isMainThread());
171 LOG(ResourceLoading, "Revalidation failed for %p", &revalidatingResource);
172 ASSERT(revalidatingResource.resourceToRevalidate());
173 revalidatingResource.clearResourceToRevalidate();
174}

176CachedResource* MemoryCache::resourceForRequest(const ResourceRequest& request, PAL::SessionID sessionID)
177{
178 // FIXME: Change all clients to make sure HTTP(s) URLs have no fragment identifiers before calling here.
179 // CachedResourceLoader is now doing this. Add an assertion once all other clients are doing it too.
180 auto* resources = sessionResourceMap(sessionID);
181 if (!resources)
182 return nullptr;
183 return resourceForRequestImpl(request, *resources);
184}
185
186CachedResource* MemoryCache::resourceForRequestImpl(const ResourceRequest& request, CachedResourceMap& resources)
187{
188 ASSERT(WTF::isMainThread());
189 URL url = removeFragmentIdentifierIfNeeded(request.url());
190
191 auto key = std::make_pair(url, request.cachePartition());
192 return resources.get(key);
193}
194
195unsigned MemoryCache::deadCapacity() const
196{
197 // Dead resource capacity is whatever space is not occupied by live resources, bounded by an independent minimum and maximum.
198 unsigned capacity = m_capacity - std::min(m_liveSize, m_capacity); // Start with available capacity.
199 capacity = std::max(capacity, m_minDeadCapacity); // Make sure it's above the minimum.
200 capacity = std::min(capacity, m_maxDeadCapacity); // Make sure it's below the maximum.
201 return capacity;
202}
203
204unsigned MemoryCache::liveCapacity() const
205{
206 // Live resource capacity is whatever is left over after calculating dead resource capacity.
207 return m_capacity - deadCapacity();
208}
209
210void MemoryCache::pruneLiveResources(bool shouldDestroyDecodedDataForAllLiveResources)
211{
212 unsigned capacity = shouldDestroyDecodedDataForAllLiveResources ? 0 : liveCapacity();
213 if (capacity && m_liveSize <= capacity)
214 return;
215
216 unsigned targetSize = static_cast<unsigned>(capacity * cTargetPrunePercentage); // Cut by a percentage to avoid immediately pruning again.
217
218 pruneLiveResourcesToSize(targetSize, shouldDestroyDecodedDataForAllLiveResources);
219}
220
221void MemoryCache::forEachResource(const WTF::Function<void(CachedResource&)>& function)
222{
223 for (auto& unprotectedLRUList : m_allResources) {
224 for (auto& resource : copyToVector(*unprotectedLRUList))
225 function(*resource);
226 }
227}
228
229void MemoryCache::forEachSessionResource(PAL::SessionID sessionID, const WTF::Function<void (CachedResource&)>& function)
230{
231 auto it = m_sessionResources.find(sessionID);
232 if (it == m_sessionResources.end())
233 return;
234
235 for (auto& resource : copyToVector(it->value->values()))
236 function(*resource);
237}

239void MemoryCache::destroyDecodedDataForAllImages()
240{
241 MemoryCache::singleton().forEachResource([](CachedResource& resource) {
242 if (!resource.isImage())
243 return;
244
245 if (auto image = downcast<CachedImage>(resource).image())
246 image->destroyDecodedData();
247 });
248}
249
250void MemoryCache::pruneLiveResourcesToSize(unsigned targetSize, bool shouldDestroyDecodedDataForAllLiveResources)
251{
252 if (m_inPruneResources)
253 return;
254
255 LOG(ResourceLoading, "MemoryCache::pruneLiveResourcesToSize(%d, shouldDestroyDecodedDataForAllLiveResources = %d)", targetSize, shouldDestroyDecodedDataForAllLiveResources);
256
257 SetForScope<bool> reentrancyProtector(m_inPruneResources, true);
258
259 MonotonicTime currentTime = FrameView::currentPaintTimeStamp();
260 if (!currentTime) // In case prune is called directly, outside of a Frame paint.
261 currentTime = MonotonicTime::now();
262
263 // Destroy any decoded data in live objects that we can.
264 // Start from the head, since this is the least recently accessed of the objects.
265
266 // The list might not be sorted by the m_lastDecodedAccessTime. The impact
267 // of this weaker invariant is minor as the below if statement to check the
268 // elapsedTime will evaluate to false as the currentTime will be a lot
269 // greater than the current->m_lastDecodedAccessTime.
270 // For more details see: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=30209
271 auto it = m_liveDecodedResources.begin();
272 while (it != m_liveDecodedResources.end()) {
273 auto* current = *it;
274
275 LOG(ResourceLoading, " live resource %p %.255s - loaded %d, decodedSize %u", current, current->url().string().utf8().data(), current->isLoaded(), current->decodedSize());
276
277 // Increment the iterator now because the call to destroyDecodedData() below
278 // may cause a call to ListHashSet::remove() and invalidate the current
279 // iterator. Note that this is safe because unlike iteration of most
280 // WTF Hash data structures, iteration is guaranteed safe against mutation
281 // of the ListHashSet, except for removal of the item currently pointed to
282 // by a given iterator.
283 ++it;
284
285 ASSERT(current->hasClients());
286 if (current->isLoaded() && current->decodedSize()) {
287 // Check to see if the remaining resources are too new to prune.
288 Seconds elapsedTime = currentTime - current->m_lastDecodedAccessTime;
289 if (!shouldDestroyDecodedDataForAllLiveResources && elapsedTime < cMinDelayBeforeLiveDecodedPrune) {
290 LOG(ResourceLoading, " current time is less than min delay before pruning (%.3fms)", elapsedTime.milliseconds());
291 return;
292 }
293
294 // Destroy our decoded data. This will remove us from m_liveDecodedResources, and possibly move us
295 // to a different LRU list in m_allResources.
296 current->destroyDecodedData();
297
298 if (targetSize && m_liveSize <= targetSize)
299 return;
300 }
301 }
302}
303
304void MemoryCache::pruneDeadResources()
305{
306 LOG(ResourceLoading, "MemoryCache::pruneDeadResources");
307
308 unsigned capacity = deadCapacity();
309 if (capacity && m_deadSize <= capacity)
310 return;
311
312 unsigned targetSize = static_cast<unsigned>(capacity * cTargetPrunePercentage); // Cut by a percentage to avoid immediately pruning again.
313 pruneDeadResourcesToSize(targetSize);
314}
315
316void MemoryCache::pruneDeadResourcesToSize(unsigned targetSize)
317{
318 if (m_inPruneResources)
319 return;
320
321 LOG(ResourceLoading, "MemoryCache::pruneDeadResourcesToSize(%d)", targetSize);
322
323 SetForScope<bool> reentrancyProtector(m_inPruneResources, true);
324
325 if (targetSize && m_deadSize <= targetSize)
326 return;
327
328 bool canShrinkLRULists = true;
329 for (int i = m_allResources.size() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
330 // Make a copy of the LRUList first (and ref the resources) as calling
331 // destroyDecodedData() can alter the LRUList.
332 auto lruList = copyToVector(*m_allResources[i]);
333
334 LOG(ResourceLoading, " lru list (size %lu) - flushing stage", lruList.size());
335
336 // First flush all the decoded data in this queue.
337 // Remove from the head, since this is the least frequently accessed of the objects.
338 for (auto& resource : lruList) {
339 LOG(ResourceLoading, " lru resource %p - in cache %d, has clients %d, preloaded %d, loaded %d", resource, resource->inCache(), resource->hasClients(), resource->isPreloaded(), resource->isLoaded());
340 if (!resource->inCache())
341 continue;
342
343 if (!resource->hasClients() && !resource->isPreloaded() && resource->isLoaded()) {
344 // Destroy our decoded data. This will remove us from
345 // m_liveDecodedResources, and possibly move us to a different
346 // LRU list in m_allResources.
347
348 LOG(ResourceLoading, " lru resource %p destroyDecodedData", resource);
349
350 resource->destroyDecodedData();
351
352 if (targetSize && m_deadSize <= targetSize)
353 return;
354 }
355 }
356
357 LOG(ResourceLoading, " lru list (size %lu) - eviction stage", lruList.size());
358
359 // Now evict objects from this list.
360 // Remove from the head, since this is the least frequently accessed of the objects.
361 for (auto& resource : lruList) {
362 LOG(ResourceLoading, " lru resource %p - in cache %d, has clients %d, preloaded %d, loaded %d", resource, resource->inCache(), resource->hasClients(), resource->isPreloaded(), resource->isLoaded());
363 if (!resource->inCache())
364 continue;
365
366 if (!resource->hasClients() && !resource->isPreloaded() && !resource->isCacheValidator()) {
367 remove(*resource);
368 if (targetSize && m_deadSize <= targetSize)
369 return;
370 }
371 }
372
373 // Shrink the vector back down so we don't waste time inspecting
374 // empty LRU lists on future prunes.
375 if (!m_allResources[i]->isEmpty())
376 canShrinkLRULists = false;
377 else if (canShrinkLRULists)
378 m_allResources.shrink(i);
379 }
380}
381
382void MemoryCache::setCapacities(unsigned minDeadBytes, unsigned maxDeadBytes, unsigned totalBytes)
383{
384 ASSERT(minDeadBytes <= maxDeadBytes);
385 ASSERT(maxDeadBytes <= totalBytes);
386 m_minDeadCapacity = minDeadBytes;
387 m_maxDeadCapacity = maxDeadBytes;
388 m_capacity = totalBytes;
389 prune();
390}
391
392void MemoryCache::remove(CachedResource& resource)
393{
394 ASSERT(WTF::isMainThread());
395 LOG(ResourceLoading, "Evicting resource %p for '%.255s' from cache", &resource, resource.url().string().latin1().data());
396 // The resource may have already been removed by someone other than our caller,
397 // who needed a fresh copy for a reload. See <http://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=12479#c6>.
398 if (auto* resources = sessionResourceMap(resource.sessionID())) {
399 auto key = std::make_pair(resource.url(), resource.cachePartition());
400
401 if (resource.inCache()) {
402 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(resource.response().source() != ResourceResponse::Source::InspectorOverride, "InspectorOverride responses should not get into the MemoryCache");
403
404 // Remove resource from the resource map.
405 resources->remove(key);
406 resource.setInCache(false);
407
408 // If the resource map is now empty, remove it from m_sessionResources.
409 if (resources->isEmpty())
410 m_sessionResources.remove(resource.sessionID());
411
412 // Remove from the appropriate LRU list.
413 removeFromLRUList(resource);
414 removeFromLiveDecodedResourcesList(resource);
415 adjustSize(resource.hasClients(), -static_cast<long long>(resource.size()));
416 } else {
417 ASSERT(resources->get(key) != &resource);
418 LOG(ResourceLoading, " resource %p is not in cache", &resource);
419 }
420 }
421
422 if (resource.canDelete())
423 resource.deleteThis();
424}
425
426auto MemoryCache::lruListFor(CachedResource& resource) -> LRUList&
427{
428 unsigned accessCount = std::max(resource.accessCount(), 1U);
429 unsigned queueIndex = WTF::fastLog2(resource.size() / accessCount);
430#if ASSERT_ENABLED
431 resource.m_lruIndex = queueIndex;
432#endif
433
434 m_allResources.reserveCapacity(queueIndex + 1);
435 while (m_allResources.size() <= queueIndex)
436 m_allResources.uncheckedAppend(makeUnique<LRUList>());
437 return *m_allResources[queueIndex];
438}
439
440void MemoryCache::removeFromLRUList(CachedResource& resource)
441{
442 // If we've never been accessed, then we're brand new and not in any list.
443 if (!resource.accessCount())
444 return;
445
446#if ASSERT_ENABLED
447 unsigned oldListIndex = resource.m_lruIndex;
448#endif
449
450 LRUList& list = lruListFor(resource);
451
452 // Verify that the list we got is the list we want.
453 ASSERT(resource.m_lruIndex == oldListIndex);
454
455 bool removed = list.remove(&resource);
456 ASSERT_UNUSED(removed, removed);
457}
458
459void MemoryCache::insertInLRUList(CachedResource& resource)
460{
461 ASSERT(resource.inCache());
462 ASSERT(resource.accessCount() > 0);
463
464 auto addResult = lruListFor(resource).add(&resource);
465 ASSERT_UNUSED(addResult, addResult.isNewEntry);
466}
467
468void MemoryCache::resourceAccessed(CachedResource& resource)
469{
470 ASSERT(resource.inCache());
471
472 // Need to make sure to remove before we increase the access count, since
473 // the queue will possibly change.
474 removeFromLRUList(resource);
475
476 // If this is the first time the resource has been accessed, adjust the size of the cache to account for its initial size.
477 if (!resource.accessCount())
478 adjustSize(resource.hasClients(), resource.size());
479
480 // Add to our access count.
481 resource.increaseAccessCount();
482
483 // Now insert into the new queue.
484 insertInLRUList(resource);
485}
486
487void MemoryCache::removeResourcesWithOrigin(SecurityOrigin& origin)
488{
489 String originPartition = ResourceRequest::partitionName(origin.host());
490
491 Vector<CachedResource*> resourcesWithOrigin;
492 for (auto& resources : m_sessionResources.values()) {
493 for (auto& keyValue : *resources) {
494 auto& resource = *keyValue.value;
495 auto& partitionName = keyValue.key.second;
496 if (partitionName == originPartition) {
497 resourcesWithOrigin.append(&resource);
498 continue;
499 }
500 auto resourceOrigin = SecurityOrigin::create(resource.url());
501 if (resourceOrigin->equal(&origin))
502 resourcesWithOrigin.append(&resource);
503 }
504 }
505
506 for (auto* resource : resourcesWithOrigin)
507 remove(*resource);
508}
509
510void MemoryCache::removeResourcesWithOrigins(PAL::SessionID sessionID, const HashSet<RefPtr<SecurityOrigin>>& origins)
511{
512 auto* resourceMap = sessionResourceMap(sessionID);
513 if (!resourceMap)
514 return;
515
516 HashSet<String> originPartitions;
517
518 for (auto& origin : origins)
519 originPartitions.add(ResourceRequest::partitionName(origin->host()));
520
521 Vector<CachedResource*> resourcesToRemove;
522 for (auto& keyValuePair : *resourceMap) {
523 auto& resource = *keyValuePair.value;
524 auto& partitionName = keyValuePair.key.second;
525 if (originPartitions.contains(partitionName)) {
526 resourcesToRemove.append(&resource);
527 continue;
528 }
529 if (origins.contains(SecurityOrigin::create(resource.url()).ptr()))
530 resourcesToRemove.append(&resource);
531 }
532
533 for (auto& resource : resourcesToRemove)
534 remove(*resource);
535}
536
537void MemoryCache::getOriginsWithCache(SecurityOriginSet& origins)
538{
539 for (auto& resources : m_sessionResources.values()) {
540 for (auto& keyValue : *resources) {
541 auto& resource = *keyValue.value;
542 auto& partitionName = keyValue.key.second;
543 if (!partitionName.isEmpty())
544 origins.add(SecurityOrigin::create("http"_s, partitionName, 0));
545 else
546 origins.add(SecurityOrigin::create(resource.url()));
547 }
548 }
549}
550
551HashSet<RefPtr<SecurityOrigin>> MemoryCache::originsWithCache(PAL::SessionID sessionID) const
552{
553 HashSet<RefPtr<SecurityOrigin>> origins;
554
555 auto it = m_sessionResources.find(sessionID);
556 if (it != m_sessionResources.end()) {
557 for (auto& keyValue : *it->value) {
558 auto& resource = *keyValue.value;
559 auto& partitionName = keyValue.key.second;
560 if (!partitionName.isEmpty())
561 origins.add(SecurityOrigin::create("http", partitionName, 0));
562 else
563 origins.add(SecurityOrigin::create(resource.url()));
564 }
565 }
566
567 return origins;
568}
569
570void MemoryCache::removeFromLiveDecodedResourcesList(CachedResource& resource)
571{
572 m_liveDecodedResources.remove(&resource);
573}
574
575void MemoryCache::insertInLiveDecodedResourcesList(CachedResource& resource)
576{
577 // Make sure we aren't in the list already.
578 ASSERT(!m_liveDecodedResources.contains(&resource));
579 m_liveDecodedResources.add(&resource);
580}
581
582void MemoryCache::addToLiveResourcesSize(CachedResource& resource)
583{
584 m_liveSize += resource.size();
585 m_deadSize -= resource.size();
586}
587
588void MemoryCache::removeFromLiveResourcesSize(CachedResource& resource)
589{
590 m_liveSize -= resource.size();
591 m_deadSize += resource.size();
592}
593
594void MemoryCache::adjustSize(bool live, long long delta)
595{
596 if (live) {
597 ASSERT(delta >= 0 || (static_cast<long long>(m_liveSize) + delta >= 0));
598 m_liveSize += delta;
599 } else {
600 ASSERT(delta >= 0 || (static_cast<long long>(m_deadSize) + delta >= 0));
601 m_deadSize += delta;
602 }
603}
604
605void MemoryCache::removeRequestFromSessionCaches(ScriptExecutionContext& context, const ResourceRequest& request)
606{
607 if (is<WorkerGlobalScope>(context)) {
608 downcast<WorkerGlobalScope>(context).thread().workerLoaderProxy().postTaskToLoader([request = request.isolatedCopy()] (ScriptExecutionContext& context) {
609 MemoryCache::removeRequestFromSessionCaches(context, request);
610 });
611 return;
612 }
613
614 auto& memoryCache = MemoryCache::singleton();
615 for (auto& resources : memoryCache.m_sessionResources) {
616 if (CachedResource* resource = memoryCache.resourceForRequestImpl(request, *resources.value))
617 memoryCache.remove(*resource);
618 }
619}
620
621void MemoryCache::TypeStatistic::addResource(CachedResource& resource)
622{
623 count++;
624 size += resource.size();
625 liveSize += resource.hasClients() ? resource.size() : 0;
626 decodedSize += resource.decodedSize();
627}
628
629MemoryCache::Statistics MemoryCache::getStatistics()
630{
631 Statistics stats;
632
633 for (auto& resources : m_sessionResources.values()) {
634 for (auto* resource : resources->values()) {
635 switch (resource->type()) {
636 case CachedResource::Type::ImageResource:
637 stats.images.addResource(*resource);
638 break;
639 case CachedResource::Type::CSSStyleSheet:
640 stats.cssStyleSheets.addResource(*resource);
641 break;
642 case CachedResource::Type::Script:
643 stats.scripts.addResource(*resource);
644 break;
645#if ENABLE(XSLT)
646 case CachedResource::Type::XSLStyleSheet:
647 stats.xslStyleSheets.addResource(*resource);
648 break;
649#endif
650 case CachedResource::Type::SVGFontResource:
651 case CachedResource::Type::FontResource:
652 stats.fonts.addResource(*resource);
653 break;
654 default:
655 break;
656 }
657 }
658 }
659 return stats;
660}
661
662void MemoryCache::setDisabled(bool disabled)
663{
664 m_disabled = disabled;
665 if (!m_disabled)
666 return;
667
668 while (!m_sessionResources.isEmpty()) {
669 auto& resources = *m_sessionResources.begin()->value;
670 ASSERT(!resources.isEmpty());
671 remove(*resources.begin()->value);
672 }
673}
674
675void MemoryCache::evictResources()
676{
677 if (disabled())
678 return;
679
680 setDisabled(true);
681 setDisabled(false);
682}
683
684void MemoryCache::evictResources(PAL::SessionID sessionID)
685{
686 if (disabled())
687 return;
688
689 forEachSessionResource(sessionID, [this] (CachedResource& resource) { remove(resource); });
690
691 ASSERT(!m_sessionResources.contains(sessionID));
692}
693
694bool MemoryCache::needsPruning() const
695{
696 return m_liveSize + m_deadSize > m_capacity || m_deadSize > m_maxDeadCapacity;
697}
698
699void MemoryCache::prune()
700{
701 if (!needsPruning())
702 return;
703
704 pruneDeadResources(); // Prune dead first, in case it was "borrowing" capacity from live.
705 pruneLiveResources();
706}
707
708void MemoryCache::pruneSoon()
709{
710 if (m_pruneTimer.isActive())
711 return;
712 if (!needsPruning())
713 return;
714 m_pruneTimer.startOneShot(0_s);
715}
716
717void MemoryCache::dumpStats()
718{
719 Statistics s = getStatistics();
720 WTFLogAlways("\nMemory Cache");
721 WTFLogAlways("%-13s %-13s %-13s %-13s %-13s\n", "", "Count", "Size", "LiveSize", "DecodedSize");
722 WTFLogAlways("%-13s %-13s %-13s %-13s %-13s\n", "-------------", "-------------", "-------------", "-------------", "-------------");
723 WTFLogAlways("%-13s %13d %13d %13d %13d\n", "Images", s.images.count, s.images.size, s.images.liveSize, s.images.decodedSize);
724 WTFLogAlways("%-13s %13d %13d %13d %13d\n", "CSS", s.cssStyleSheets.count, s.cssStyleSheets.size, s.cssStyleSheets.liveSize, s.cssStyleSheets.decodedSize);
725#if ENABLE(XSLT)
726 WTFLogAlways("%-13s %13d %13d %13d %13d\n", "XSL", s.xslStyleSheets.count, s.xslStyleSheets.size, s.xslStyleSheets.liveSize, s.xslStyleSheets.decodedSize);
727#endif
728 WTFLogAlways("%-13s %13d %13d %13d %13d\n", "JavaScript", s.scripts.count, s.scripts.size, s.scripts.liveSize, s.scripts.decodedSize);
729 WTFLogAlways("%-13s %13d %13d %13d %13d\n", "Fonts", s.fonts.count, s.fonts.size, s.fonts.liveSize, s.fonts.decodedSize);
730 WTFLogAlways("%-13s %-13s %-13s %-13s %-13s\n\n", "-------------", "-------------", "-------------", "-------------", "-------------");
731
732 unsigned countTotal = s.images.count + s.cssStyleSheets.count + s.scripts.count + s.fonts.count;
733 unsigned sizeTotal = s.images.size + s.cssStyleSheets.size + s.scripts.size + s.fonts.size;
734 unsigned liveSizeTotal = s.images.liveSize + s.cssStyleSheets.liveSize + s.scripts.liveSize + s.fonts.liveSize;
735 unsigned decodedSizeTotal = s.images.decodedSize + s.cssStyleSheets.decodedSize + s.scripts.decodedSize + s.fonts.decodedSize;
736#if ENABLE(XSLT)
737 countTotal += s.xslStyleSheets.count;
738 sizeTotal += s.xslStyleSheets.size;
739 liveSizeTotal += s.xslStyleSheets.liveSize;
740 decodedSizeTotal += s.xslStyleSheets.decodedSize;
741#endif
742
743 WTFLogAlways("%-13s %13d %11.2fKB %11.2fKB %11.2fKB\n", "Total", countTotal, sizeTotal / 1024., liveSizeTotal / 1024., decodedSizeTotal / 1024.);
744}
745
746void MemoryCache::dumpLRULists(bool includeLive) const
747{
748 WTFLogAlways("LRU-SP lists in eviction order (Kilobytes decoded, Kilobytes encoded, Access count, Referenced):\n");
749
750 int size = m_allResources.size();
751 for (int i = size - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
752 WTFLogAlways("\nList %d:\n", i);
753 for (auto* resource : *m_allResources[i]) {
754 if (includeLive || !resource->hasClients())
755 WTFLogAlways(" %p %.255s %.1fK, %.1fK, accesses: %u, clients: %d\n", resource, resource->url().string().utf8().data(), resource->decodedSize() / 1024.0f, (resource->encodedSize() + resource->overheadSize()) / 1024.0f, resource->accessCount(), resource->numberOfClients());
756 }
757 }
758}
